title: Malaysia Employed Persons
description: The number of employed persons in Malaysia increased to 16050 Thousand in September of 2022 from 16017.70 Thousand in August of 2022. Employed Persons in Malaysia averaged 13235.18 Thousand from 1985 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 16050 Thousand in September of 2022 and a record low of 5624.60 Thousand in December of 1985. In Malaysia, employed persons are individuals with a minimum required age who work during a certain time for a business. This page provides - Malaysia Employed Persons - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Department of Statistics, Malaysia
